description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Practitioner Sonographer Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Radiology / Ultrasound Department &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tameside &amp; Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust provides hospital services for children and adults across Tameside and Glossop. The Trust is situated at the foot of the Pennines, six miles to the east of Manchester and serves a population of approximately 250,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There has never been a more exciting time to join us. Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust (T&amp;G IC) provides the foundation for one of the first ICOs in England, bringing together a wide range of health and social care services for the benefit of local people. The ICO will manage a person’s entire care in the future, by linking up hospital services with community care and mental health services as well as working closely with GPs and we are well on our way to fully transforming our services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having gone through a period of intense scrutiny and special measures, Tameside is now proud to have achieved and maintained the overall CQC rating as a &lt;strong&gt;GOOD&lt;/strong&gt; organisation with some outstanding areas of practice following our recent inspection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values and behaviours are at the heart of everything we do, and the Trust’s values and behaviours drive a culture of openness and candour, where staff are listened to and where patients come first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dedicated Sonographer, with excellent clinical skills to join our friendly and progressive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are a new sonographer looking for that first step into an acute environment or an experienced sonographer looking to broaden your skill set Tameside Hospital has a wealth of opportunities to offer you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tameside Ultrasound department is a forward thinking department which has undergone significant transformation in recent years. There has been investment in ultrasound equipment and in clinical and managerial support from the Radiologists, and radiology management team. We are one of the only trusts in the North West to have a Consultant Sonographer who heads the department and offers mentorship, clinical support to Sonographer team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tameside Hospital promotes and supports continued professional development in a supportive learning environment; we encourage and pay for attendance at relevant study days and national conferences such as BMUS / UKRC. There are also a successful monthly Ultrasound interesting case &amp; Gynaecology meetings as well as quarterly Radiology Audit meetings. We believe in peer review and have a successful NT peer review monthly assessment; peer review audit tool is being introduced to include Non obstetric work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Obstetric ultrasound department is equipped with 3 modern ultrasound rooms all with dedicated GE PACS viewing monitors. There is a dedicated Obstetric ultrasound reporting room with voice recognition and PACS facility. Our Ultrasound equipment is state of the art , high specification equipment , there are 3 Canon Aplio 500 scanners, 1 with 3/4D scanning facilities. We undertake a full range of Obstetric Ultrasound examination, and are one of the few units in to be compliant with RCOG guidance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Managing Small for Dates Babies and have one of the lowest stillborn rates in the country. We have close collaboration with our Midwifery Ultrasound service and support a Fetal Medicine ultrasound service. We are a training site for University of Salford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a Siemens S2000 dedicated to early pregnancy on our Women’s Health Unit, there will be a commitment to partake in the Sonographer led weekend early pregnancy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are 3 ultrasound rooms in the main Radiology department using the HSS Radiology CRIS system. The ultrasound equipment has 2 Siemens systems including a S2000 Helx equipped with Elastography and a Siemens S2000 equipped with 3D scanning. This department undertakes a wide range of non-obstetric ultrasound scans including inpatients, MSK, Head and Neck, Paediatrics and interventional procedures, Sonographers have a dedicated dual screen PACS reporting room with voice recognition and secretarial support and dedicated healthcare assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Sonographer team lead the point of care ultrasound service on the Acute Medical Unit an innovative approach to seeing the patient as the bedside, this has been operational for 5 years, using a Canon Aplio A450 with SMI technology which is wifi enabled. We also provide the Cranial Ultrasound service on the Special Care Baby Unit using a GE Vivid SE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In terms of extended scope of practice, we have 2 Sonographers undertaking Head and Neck ultrasound including interventional techniques such as FNA’s and aspirations. We are also in the process of extending the scope of the entire team to perform simple MSK scanning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will rotate through the department maintaining your skills in obstetric, early pregnancy, gynaecology and general medicine scanning (following a preceptorship period if needed). There is scope for interested Sonographers in developing their skills in other areas such as Paediatric Hips, Neonatal cranial ultrasound, Head and Neck ultrasound including interventional techniques such as FNA’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why Tameside?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Everyone Matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Protected CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern US Equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will consider applications for Band 7 from candidates who are newly qualified.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a requirement of this post that the successful candidate can be registered with the Fetal Medicine Foundation as a DQASS accredited Sonographer. &lt;span&gt;In view of this, applicants who do not hold the accredited qualification, need not apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHelen Johnson&lt;/p&gt;
